#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code longest valid parentheses substring nikalne ke liye stack of indices use karta hai.

1. Stack me initially -1 push karte hain.
   Ye base index ki tarah kaam karta hai for length calculation.
2. String ko left se right traverse karte hain.
3. Agar '(' mile, to uska index stack me push kar do.
4. Agar ')' mile, to stack ka top pop kar do
   kyuki ek opening bracket ko match karne ki koshish ho rahi hai.
5. Pop ke baad:
   - agar stack empty ho gaya, to current index push kar do
     (ye new invalid base ban jaata hai)
   - warna valid substring ki length = i - stack.peek()
6. Har baar maxLen update karte rehte hain.

Main idea:
Stack unmatched brackets ke indices store karta hai.
Jab valid pair milta hai, to current index aur stack ke top ke beech ka gap
valid parentheses substring ki length deta hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.*;
public class Solution
{
    public int longestValidParentheses(String s)
    {
        //You can code here

        int n = s.length();
        int maxLen = 0;
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        stack.push(-1);

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
          char ch = s.charAt(i);

          if(ch == '('){
            stack.push(i);
          }
          else{
            stack.pop();
            if(stack.isEmpty()){
              stack.push(i);
            }
            else{
              int len = i - stack.peek();
              maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, len);
            }
          }
        }
        return maxLen;      
    }
}
